        {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Introduction to Metals Used in Mobile Phones",
            "subtitle": "Overview of Metallic Components",
            "blocks": [
                {
                    "kind": "paragraph",
                    "text": "Modern mobile phones are complex electronic devices composed of numerous metallic elements. These metals are essential for structural integrity, electrical conductivity, energy storage, and functional performance. Understanding the role of metals provides insight into both technological advancement and material science."
                },
                {
                    "kind": "bullets",
                    "items": [
                        "Metals as fundamental building blocks of smartphones",
                        "Wide range of metallic elements involved",
                        "Critical role in electronic and mechanical functions"
                    ]
