            "subtitle": "Transparent Conductive Materials",
            "blocks": [
                {
                    "kind": "paragraph",
                    "text": "Indium is primarily used in the form of indium tin oxide (ITO), which is a transparent and conductive material. It is essential for touchscreens, allowing displays to respond accurately to user interaction while maintaining optical clarity."
                },
                {
                    "kind": "bullets",
                    "items": [
